	 <zoopedia_light_mm>
	  <entry>Tank Light</entry>
	 <text>
		<cell pady="0" width="1000"/>
		<p/>
		<cell width="260"/>
		<cell width="640" height="320" bgimg="ui/zoopedia/topCellBg.dds">
		 <cell width="600" padx="20" pady="20">
		  <color r="255" g="255" b="255">
			<img src="entities/objects/scenery/light_mm/light_mm_icon.dds" sx="0" sy="0" sw="64" sh="64"/>
			<p/>Tank lights illuminate the water inside marine tanks. You can also use them to light murky benthic or wetlands exhibits.
			<p/>The tank light is available for purchase after winning the Show Tycoon Level 1 Award.
		  </color>
		 </cell>
		</cell>
	  </text>  
	 </zoopedia_light_mm>
	 
	 <zoopedia_tankportal>
	  <entry>Tank Portal</entry>
	 <text>
		<cell pady="0" width="1000"/>
		<p/>
		<cell width="260"/>
		<cell width="640" height="320" bgimg="ui/zoopedia/topCellBg.dds">
		 <cell width="600" padx="20" pady="20">
		  <color r="255" g="255" b="255">
			<img src="entities/objects/fences/AnimalTank_Gate/AnimalTank_Gate_icon.dds" sx="0" sy="0" sw="64" sh="64"/>
			<p/>Tank portals connect marine show tanks to regular exhibit tanks. Show animals cannot live all the time in a show tank. You must create an exhibit tank for show animals to live in when they finish performing. Place an exhibit tank adjacent to a show tank and connect them with a tank portal. When it's time for a show, animals travel from the exhibit tank to the show tank via the tank portal.
		  </color>
		 </cell>
		</cell>
	  </text>  
	 </zoopedia_tankportal>
	 
	 <zoopedia_trainingarea>
	  <entry>Training Area</entry>
	 <text>
		<cell pady="0" width="1000"/>
		<p/>
		<cell width="260"/>
		<cell width="640" height="320" bgimg="ui/zoopedia/topCellBg.dds">
		 <cell width="600" padx="20" pady="20">
		  <color r="255" g="255" b="255">
			<img src="entities/objects/props/TrainingArea/TrainingArea_mm_icon.dds" sx="0" sy="0" sw="64" sh="64"/>
			<p/>Training areas are used for training marine animals tricks to perform in marine shows. You must place a training area and a tank entrance in a tank to train the animals in it.
		  </color>
		 </cell>
		</cell>
	  </text>  
	 </zoopedia_trainingarea>
	 
	 <zoopedia_trickarea_mm>
